      <h2>Who are the Miccosukee?</h2>
      <p>

 		The Miccosukee Tribe of Indians of Florida is a federally recognized Native American tribe in the U.S. state of Florida. They were part of the Seminole nation until the mid-20th century, when they organized as an independent tribe, receiving federal recognition in 1962. The Miccosukee speak the Mikasuki language. There are 600 members of the Miccosukee Indian Nation.

 		The Miccosukee Indian Nation are the owners of the Miccosukee Resort & Gaming business, and others.

      </p>

