      <h2>Mikasuki Language and its Importance</h2>
      <p>
        The Mikasuki language is spoken by them and other members of the Seminole Indian Nation. 90% of them are fluent in Miccosukee, and only a few are monolingual in Mikasuki and the rest speak English.

      	However, ten years ago it was spoken only by a 100 members. There is a lack of language knowledge and resources and this page is created to help create awareness about the Miccosukees and their language.

      	Losing the Mikasuki language, any language, means we lose an enormous cultural heritage, and most importantly we lose the expression of the community humor, love and tradition. We lose the testimony of centuries of life.

      </p>

